By Crispine Otieno Police in Kisii have launched investigations after a middle-aged man hacked his wife and two children in Gesoni village Mosocho in Kisii, in a suspected domestic feud before surrendering to the police Nyatieko Police station within Kisii township. Confirming the incident, Kisii Coujty Police commander Francis Kooli  said that Daniel Asiago committed the heinous act on Sunday evening, after which villagers reacted by torching his three bedroom semi-permanent  house. The three family members were later rushed to Kisii teaching and referral hospital in critical condition for emergency medical care. The suspect continues to be interrogated at Nyatieko police station.